==Billboard Music Award==
The [[Billboard Music Award]]s are sponsored by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine and is held annually in December. The awards are based on sales data by [[Nielsen SoundScan]] and radio information by [[Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems]].<ref>Jeckell, Barry A. ([[December 7]] [[2005]]). [http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1001615496 50 Cent, Green Day Reap Major Billboard Music Awards]. ''Billboard''. Accessed on [[November 9]] [[2007]].</ref> 50 Cent has received thirteen awards and five nominations.

